      <p>So interesting. Iâ€™m so glad youâ€™ve climbed this mountain. My own revelation with polenta came when I used Rozanne Goldâ€™s recipe from Recipes &#8211; One Two Three ages ago. Despite EVERY other recipe at the time, she started with cornmeal in the pot and added liquid to THAT, rather than adding the cornmeal to the liquid. THATâ€™S the secret. Iâ€™ve never understood why anyone would do it any other way. Youâ€™re not fighting to keep the lumps down this way.  I guess that&#39;s kind of Bittman&#39;s recipe.</p>
<p>Ina Garten loves that boiling water method for keeping mashed potatoes hot. It does work really well with polenta too. </p>
