    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>my mom is Italian, and we were practically weaned on polenta. We serve it with roast and brown gravy. After it&#39;s cooked, we pour it onto a cutting board, cover with a towel and then slice with a serrated knife. The next day, cut the leftover polenta into chunks and fry them in butter. Crispy on the outside and soft on the inside. Truly, there&#39;s nothing better!</p>
    </div>

