    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I lovelovelove polenta. Warm and liquid or cooled and grilled. I learned to make it in Italy, where they told me that the instructions to stir polenta (and risotto) constantly were invented to keep your mother in law out of your hair while you cooked the rest of the dinner. LOL! Ever since then I&#39;ve just stirred it every few minutes&#8230;</p>
<p>I love to add a big handful of parmesan to it. I love the flavor that adds to it. </p>
<p>Thank you for this recipe and the reminder of this wonderful dish.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-17753' data-commentid="17753" data-postid="860" data-belowelement="comment-17753" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kate at Serendipity" aria-label='Reply to Kate at Serendipity'>Reply</a>    </div>
