  <li id="comment-17779" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">clickychick</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2010/03/a-reasonable-question/#comment-17779"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-03-07T19:39:41-05:00">Sunday, March 7, 2010 at 7:39 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Once I discovered the polenta-in-the-oven method, I&#39;ve never looked back.  So insanely easy.  No more tubes!  ðŸ™‚  I also once, in a pinch, followed directions on a polenta package for (gasp!) polenta finished in the microwave. Seriously not bad. Too bad I just had brunch or I&#39;d be making our weekend favorite&#8211;creamy polenta topped with shaved parmesan, diced tomatoes, chiffonade basil, oven-made bacon (another technique that changed my cooking life) and two eggs over easy.  Best. breakfast. ever.</p>
