      <a href="https://orangette.net/2010/03/a-reasonable-question/#comment-17794"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-03-07T22:41:40-05:00">Sunday, March 7, 2010 at 10:41 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>My fav polenta recipe of the moment is from Peter Berley&#39;s Flexitarian Table cookbook.  The main addition is fresh corn, right after the cornmeal/water mix comes back up to a bubble. I use corn that I froze last summer, straight from the freezer.  It adds super-sweet nubbly bits that contrast so nicely with the creamy-nutty base.  Plus if there is a lump or two, no one notices so much since the corn adds texture ðŸ™‚  Finish with some white beans or quick-saute shrimp in sage and butter sauce and you can survive these last few days of grey before spring really arrives!</p>
    </div>

