    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>My grandmother is Italian and she always pour cold water over her dry polenta before putting it in the boiling water. Works like a charm. She also has a special stick that she uses to stir it with and cooks it in a copper pan. I don&#39;t have either of those special tools and never have a problem with lumpy polenta.</p>
