    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>My mom used to make me something like sweet polenta that is popular in Brazil.  It is essentially milk, sugar, a touch of salt, and cornmeal.  All of that in a pot and stirred until thick.  I&#39;ve made it after moving out, and I have to say, it only took me about 10 minutes of stirring to get it just right.  It&#39;s a perfect breakfast.</p>
    </div>

