      <p>Regarding the plastic: What did various cultures around the world do BEFORE plastic? Examples of things being steamed or put in a double boiler that use plastic wrap now are &#8211; Chinese turnip cake, Thai sticky rice &#8211; what was used before plastic? leaves, maybe? Like banana leaves? A damp cloth? </p>
<p>And I was just researching how to make little Persian rice cookies, and the dough for those go in plastic wrap overnight.</p>
