    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I just tried this recipe after a long, bad day at work.  The ratio of water to cornmeal is just right, and the texture came out perfectly creamy &#8211; and I&#39;ve never made polenta before!  The only thing is, no matter how much salt and butter I added, it just didn&#39;t seem to have a heckuva lot of flavor. Then inspiration struck and I stirred in just a tiny amount of sriracha &#8211; maybe a teaspoon for the whole pot. Instant savory perfection.</p>
