  <li id="comment-17908" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/11169500674505410526" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Roo de Loo</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2010/03/a-reasonable-question/#comment-17908"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-08-11T02:51:17-04:00">Thursday, August 11, 2011 at 2:51 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I thought only annoying parents refer to things in &#8220;months&#8221; once they get past 12 &#8211; but I find myself saying that 17 months after your original post, I followed your proprietary polenta preparation and it came off without a hitch. </p>
<p>I tripled the recipe (I&#39;m private-chefing for a bunch of yogis at Good Commons in Vermont) and the proportions were great, using a combination of homemade veg stock and water and finishing with some almond milk at the end. A hefty dash of salt, pepper, nutmeg and fresh thyme was added. To transcend from hospital food to vegan nirvana, I topped it off with wild mushroom friccassee. Yum.</p>
    </div>

